{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "20", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "33", "S": "12"}}, "news": [{"title": "India's flexible market powers through global challenges", "para": "Amidst global economic turbulence and geopolitical tensions, India's flexible workspace sector is demonstrating remarkable resilience.  Escalating uncertainties are paradoxically accelerating the shift towards agile solutions, with flex spaces becoming a strategic imperative.  This segment is carving its own growth trajectory, capturing significant market share and positioning itself as a vital enabler for businesses.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/brand-connect-initiative/indias-flexible-workspace-sector-thrives-amid-global-economic-turbulence/131219236?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-32356/131219236.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "brand-connect-initiative"}, {"title": "PMAY scam: Lokayukta raids expose \u20b929 crore fake billing in Belagavi", "para": "Karnataka Lokayukta raided officials of the Slum Development Board and a private contractor in Belagavi for alleged large-scale irregularities and fake billing in the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban). Investigations revealed collusion to generate fraudulent bills for non-existent houses, leading to the alleged misappropriation of Rs 23.3 crore.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/karnataka-lokayukta-exposes-29-crore-pmay-scam-in-belagavi/131218921?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-109242/131218921.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Pune: Experts fear property prices may rise \u20b9250-300 per sq ft if RMC suppliers go ahead with proposed hike", "para": "Ready-mix concrete suppliers in Pune have proposed a rate hike, potentially increasing construction costs by Rs 250-500 per sqft. This could lead to higher property prices for new launches as developers face challenges absorbing rising input costs. While some developers may absorb initial increases, future projects may see price corrections to maintain viability in the price-sensitive market.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/pune-experts-fear-property-prices-may-rise-250-300-per-sq-ft-if-rmc-suppliers-go-ahead-with-proposed-hike/131218802?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-70412/131218802.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}